Hey all,<br><br>
That was quick. I found this posted on the Usenet Newsgroup soc.history.war.vietnam. As I stated, I know Anne and Bob very well. I urge you to browse this site. I haven't been there in a while but I have a name or two listed. <br><br>
&quot;Empty Chairs&quot; is an internet site dedicated exclusively to Vietnam<br>
Veterans from around the world. It is a respected, and sacred location,<br>
where Veterans can post the names, details, and messages to, *all* of his,<br>
or her, friends that were &quot;Killed In Action&quot; during the Vietnam War. <br><br>
In essence, it becomes your own miniature Wall, with all the names in<br>
*one* place for simple access. <br><br>
If one needs to, they can first locate the names and statistics of<br>
individuals Killed In Action at: http://www.no- quarter.org, or any other<br>
internet &quot;Wall&quot; location. <br><br>
Veterans can then transfer them to the &quot;Empty Chairs&quot; Homepage by<br>
submitting them by regular email.  The names, messages, and details, will<br>
then be copied and posted under the first letter of *your* last name. <br><br>
*Should one wish to remain anonymous, the request will be honored.*<br><br>
In effect, a *Veteran* can then create their own &quot;Miniature Wall&quot;, which<br>
can be visited at any time. It becomes your personal listing, without<br>
having to type in one name at a time! <br><br>
Please visit The &quot;Empty Chairs&quot; Homepage at:<br><br>
http://members.aol.com/mountnman7/mtchairs.htm<br><br>
The above URL has a MIDI file embedded.<br><br>
The alternate URL, without the MIDI, can be visited at:<br><br>
http://pw2.netcom.com/~mntinman/emptychairs/mtchairs.htm<br><br>

